  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded (flow rate 1–7 L/min, impeller speed 2 000–4 500 RPM, hematocrit 35–45 %, temperature 36–38 °C, outlet pressure 60–120 mmHg). Validation dataset densely covers the declared envelope across 25 operating points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed across all five QoI hemolysis index outputs. Decision: Accepted.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
